ANTHRAX - INDIA (15): (TRIPURA) ZOO RHINOCEROS
**********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 11 Dec 2014
Source: Times of India [edited]
http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/guwahati/Tripura-zoo-rhino-dies-of-anthrax/articleshow/45480722.cms?prtpage=1


The sole male rhino at Tripura's Sepahijala Zoo died on Wednesday night [10 Dec 2014]. Zoo director Krishna Gopal Roy said the 25-year-old rhino died of anthrax. Roy said zoo keepers saw the rhino, which was bleeding, collapse on Wednesday evening. Medical help was sought but the rhino succumbed [died] on Wednesday night. A detailed investigation by a joint team of veterinary and wildlife officials on Thursday afternoon [11 Dec 2014] confirmed anthrax to be the cause of death, Roy said. There will not be any autopsy [sic] on the rhino as per anthrax protocol.

The animal had been brought to Tripura from Assam Zoo in 1994.

Pradip will be buried on Friday [12 Dec 2014].

